## 📌 The Golden Rule — Always Start Here

> Before jumping to any fix, run these 3 commands **in order**

```bash
# Step 1 — See WHAT is wrong
kubectl get pods -n <namespace>

# Step 2 — See WHY it's wrong
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>

# Step 3 — See WHAT crashed
kubectl logs <pod-name> -n <namespace> --previous
```

> 💡 **Interview Tip:** Always say — *"First I check pod status → describe → then logs"*
> That 3-step flow is what interviewers want to hear ✅

