## 1. 🔴 Pod Not Starting

**Symptom:** Pod stuck in `Pending` or `ContainerCreating`

```bash
# Check pod status
kubectl get pods -n <namespace>

# Full details + events
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>

# Check recent events in namespace
kubectl get events -n <namespace> --sort-by='.lastTimestamp'
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ Missing Secret or ConfigMap
- ❌ Not enough CPU/Memory on node
- ❌ Init container failing

---

## 2. 🌐 Service Not Accessible

**Symptom:** App is running but can't be reached via browser or API

```bash
# List services
kubectl get svc -n <namespace>

# Check endpoints — if EMPTY, labels don't match!
kubectl get endpoints <service-name> -n <namespace>

# Quick local test via port-forward
kubectl port-forward svc/<service-name> 8080:80 -n <namespace>
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ Pod labels don't match service selector
- ❌ Wrong `targetPort` in service YAML
- ❌ NetworkPolicy blocking traffic

---

## 3. 💾 PVC Not Bound

**Symptom:** Pod stuck in `Pending` — storage not attached

```bash
# Check PVC status
kubectl get pvc -n <namespace>

# Check available Persistent Volumes
kubectl get pv

# Get full details
kubectl describe pvc <pvc-name> -n <namespace>
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ No matching PV available
- ❌ StorageClass not installed
- ❌ PV is in `Released` state

---

## 4. ⚙️ ConfigMap Key Missing

**Symptom:** Pod fails or env variable shows empty value

```bash
# List ConfigMaps
kubectl get configmap -n <namespace>

# View all keys inside ConfigMap
kubectl describe configmap <cm-name> -n <namespace>

# Check env inside running pod
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -n <namespace> -- env | grep <KEY_NAME>
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ Typo in key name in pod YAML
- ❌ ConfigMap in wrong namespace
- ❌ Pod not restarted after ConfigMap update

