## 5. 🔁 CrashLoopBackOff

**Symptom:** Pod keeps restarting — Kubernetes gives up and shows `CrashLoopBackOff`

```bash
# Most important — logs from PREVIOUS crash
kubectl logs <pod-name> -n <namespace> --previous

# Full pod details
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ App crashes on startup (missing env vars, DB unreachable)
- ❌ Liveness probe killing pod too early
- ❌ Out of Memory (`OOMKilled`)

---

## 6. 🖼️ ImagePullBackOff

**Symptom:** Kubernetes can't pull the container image

```bash
# Check error in events
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>

# Verify image name and tag in deployment
kubectl get deployment <deploy-name> -n <namespace> -o yaml | grep image

# Check if image pull secret exists
kubectl get secret -n <namespace>
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ Wrong image name or tag (e.g. `latest` deleted)
- ❌ Private registry — no `imagePullSecret` set
- ❌ Docker Hub rate limit hit

---

## 7. 🖥️ Node Not Ready

**Symptom:** `kubectl get nodes` shows `NotReady`

```bash
# Check all nodes
kubectl get nodes

# Detailed condition check
kubectl describe node <node-name>

# Check CPU/Memory usage
kubectl top node
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ Kubelet service crashed on the node
- ❌ Disk full (`/var/lib/docker` or containerd)
- ❌ Network plugin (CNI) not running

---

## 8. ⏳ Pod Stuck in Pending

**Symptom:** Pod never gets scheduled to any node

```bash
# Check why pod can't be scheduled
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>

# Check node labels for nodeSelector match
kubectl get nodes --show-labels

# Check node taints
kubectl get nodes -o custom-columns=NAME:.metadata.name,TAINTS:.spec.taints
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ Pod requests more CPU/Memory than available
- ❌ Node has a taint but pod has no toleration
- ❌ `nodeSelector` doesn't match any node label

