## 9. 🔐 RBAC Forbidden Error

**Symptom:** `Error from server (Forbidden)` when accessing resources

```bash
# Check if a service account has permission
kubectl auth can-i get pods \
  --as=system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:<sa-name> \
  -n <namespace>

# List role bindings in namespace
kubectl get rolebindings -n <namespace>

# See who is bound to what role
kubectl describe rolebinding <rb-name> -n <namespace>
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ ServiceAccount has no RoleBinding
- ❌ Using wrong namespace in binding
- ❌ ClusterRole needs ClusterRoleBinding, not RoleBinding

---

## 10. 🌍 Ingress Not Working

**Symptom:** Domain returns `404`, `502`, or just times out

```bash
# Check Ingress rules
kubectl get ingress -n <namespace>

# Full Ingress details — backend + rules
kubectl describe ingress <ingress-name> -n <namespace>

# Check Ingress controller is running
kubectl get pods -n ingress-nginx

# Check IngressClass is set
kubectl get ingressclass
```

**Common Reasons:**
- ❌ `ingressClassName` not set in YAML
- ❌ Backend service name or port is wrong
- ❌ TLS secret missing or expired
- ❌ Ingress controller pod crashed

