## ⚡ 5 Commands Every Fresher Must Know

```bash
# 1. See all pods in every namespace
kubectl get pods -A

# 2. Full details of a pod (events, status, config)
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>

# 3. Crash logs from previous container run
kubectl logs <pod-name> -n <namespace> --previous

# 4. Timeline of all events — what happened and when
kubectl get events -n <namespace> --sort-by='.lastTimestamp'

# 5. Restart a deployment (quick rolling fix)
kubectl rollout restart deployment/<deploy-name> -n <namespace>
```

